# ARCHITECTURE & DESIGN RULES
## CORE PHILOSOPHY
Decoupled, scalable, and resilient systems utilizing composition and clear boundaries.

## STRUCTURAL PATTERNS
- Adhere strictly to SOLID principles and Clean Architecture concepts.
- Isolate Business Logic (Domain) from I/O, UI, and external services (Ports & Adapters pattern).
- Favor Composition over Inheritance to prevent rigid hierarchies.
- Maintain unidirectional data flow where applicable; centralize and protect state mutation.

## MODULE BOUNDARIES
- Design modules as black boxes: expose minimal public APIs, hide implementation details.
- Prevent circular dependencies via strict dependency inversion.
- Cross-module communication must happen via defined interfaces or event buses, never direct state access.

## RESILIENCE & OBSERVABILITY
- Design for failure: implement retries, timeouts, and circuit breakers for external calls.
- Standardize logging, metrics, and tracing hooks at the architectural level.
- Ensure all modules are horizontally scalable and stateless where possible.